<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="563" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1335,1685]" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1335,1360]" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[279,474,1337,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororia">
<emphasis box="[279,474,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Peromyia sororia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a single male that differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1107,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis box="[991,1107,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">P. leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an extremely similar species redescribed above, in the following characters. The new 
<taxonomicName box="[788,896,1373,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[788,896,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Peromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger, with a body length of 
<quantity box="[1255,1344,1372,1397]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="563" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
; the eye bridge is somewhat longer, namely 5 ommatidia long dorsally; the short palpus is 3-segmented, all segments the same length and bearing hair-shaped translucent sensilla; the medial whorl of translucent sensilla on the flagellomeres is situated distally of, not intermingled with, the basal setae (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1123,1479,1504]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1094,1116]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,204,1067]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[159,1430,195,1075]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10 A – B. Peromyia sororia, male (holotype). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scales for A – B, 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265197/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
); wing veins are of normal strength, not unusually weak; and the gonostylus is slightly longer and less bent (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1164,1516,1541]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1094,1116]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,204,1067]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[159,1430,195,1075]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10 A – B. Peromyia sororia, male (holotype). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scales for A – B, 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265197/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="563" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1335,1685]" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1551,1576]" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName box="[575,656,1553,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororia">
<emphasis box="[575,656,1553,1576]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">sororia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is the Latin adjective for sororal, in reference to the similarity with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,355,1588,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis box="[151,355,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="563">Peromyia leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
